node.text: When it's too hot out to turn on your oven, the time is right to experience the phenomenal crisp texture and flavor of grilled pizza. Our own Martin @breadwright is making Neapolitan-Style pizzas with our ‘00’ Pizza Flour and @BelGioiosoCheese, so fire up your grill, grab your ingredients, and join in on the fun!

Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text: Think cinnamon rolls are out of your baking wheelhouse? Think again! Our own Kye @life.of.kye is here to take you step-by-step through our #recipeoftheyear, Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls. With a friend by your virtual side, you’re destined for cinnamon-swirled success! Share your rolls with #recipeoftheyear and #KingArthurBaking

node.title: Bake it Better with Kye: How to make Perfectly Pillowy Cinnamon Rolls

node.accessibility_caption: A beet red challah on a towel. Photo shared with permission by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Beet-dyed challah is the red-hot new trend in bread baking, and there’s no one better than challah expert and bread artist, Cheryl Holbert of @nomadbakery, to show us how to recreate it. With brilliant purple dough and a shiny reddish-pink loaf, beet-dyed challah is a showstopper — no questions asked. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to see how it’s made, and share your loaf with #KingArthurBaking

Two pink challah doughs ready to be baked. Photo shared with permission by King Arthur Baking.
A fresh baked pizza on a board. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: “The best pizza you’ll ever make” is a bold title, but it’s the one our Artisan No-Knead Pizza Crust has been dubbed by many a pizza lover. With a chewy, airy crust and deep flavor (thanks to a long fermentation), this Roman-style pizza gets its inspiration from the popular wood-fired pizzerias of the West Coast. See how it’s baked to cheesy perfection at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your pizza with #KingArthurBaking

Hands working pizza dough on a table. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
Hands working pizza dough in the air. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
Grating cheese over a baked pizza. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
A fresh baked pizza ready for serving. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
A baker weighing out ingredients on a scale. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text:
We were thrilled to partner with the incredible team from @together_we_bake in Washington D.C. through our program, For Goodness Bakes. They shared:

“Together We Bake is a job training and personal development program for underserved women. Our recipe for success prepares women to enter the workforce confident and empowered!

“We selected the @BGCGW to partner with because we have previously worked with them and the kids love our cookies! We donated our chocolate chip cookies, cinnamon pecan granola, and cinnamon apple chips.” 

To learn more about the comprehensive workforce training and personal development programs of Together We Bake or the Boys and Girls Club of Alexandria, tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking

A baker with a package of cookies ready to be delivered. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
A baker in front of the delivery van holding a box in one hand and bag in the other. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
A group of kids in front of a brick building. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking
Squares of homemade marshmallows lightly coated in confectioners’ sugar, on a piece of natural parchment paper.  -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: Crackling campfires, twinkling fireflies, and the greatest of handheld treats — the s’more — are what summer dreams are made of. As we celebrate #NationalSmoresDay, we’re going all in and whipping up a batch of homemade marshmallows. Go with classic vanilla or mix up your batch by stirring in a bit of your favorite extract or flavoring. Find the recipe linked in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your National S’mores Day bites with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A group of delicious vegan apple kolaches. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: No need to wait for the fair to come around to enjoy the perfect duo that is apples and caramel. This #vegan (though you’d never guess it!) twist on classic kolaches from @sarahashey of @kingskolache features an ultra-smooth caramel made from coconut cream and LOTS of juicy apples. Find the recipe and watch it made on the Flour Finals by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking. Share your kolaches with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A tray of miscellaneous bagels ready for breakfast. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: To check one looming item off the back-to-school list this year, we’ve gathered some of our favorite make-ahead breakfast recipes for quick, scrumptious morning bites on the go. From Whole-Grain Banana Bread and hearty Bran Muffins to spiced Cinnamon Pinwheel Biscuits and these chewy Montreal Bagels, you’ll get months of weekly menu ideas when you peruse this collection. Find it and our Montreal Bagels recipe linked in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your favorite quick breakfast bakes with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A sandwich made from high rising gluten free bread. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: You may think it’s impossible to make #GlutenFree bread that rivals a standard loaf. But our recipe for Gluten-Free Sandwich Bread didn’t earn its high rating and nearly 300 reviews for nothing. Tender, high-rising, and tasty, we’re here to show you how to make a gluten-free loaf you’ll want to bake again and again. Tap the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking to check it out, and show off your loaf with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A berry dumpling treat in a cast iron skillet. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: The enticing draw of chicken and dumplings is, of course, the humble dumpling. Soft, tender, and happily bobbing in a simmering pot of tasty goodness. A sweet spin on the original, serve this NEW recipe for Berry Dumplings for dessert with a scoop of ice cream or for breakfast with a sprinkle of cinnamon-sugar. Try it for yourself at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and show us how it turns out with #KingArthurBaking

node.accessibility_caption: A berry dumpling treat in a cast iron skillet. Photo by King Arthur Baking.
A plate full of tangy berry dumplings. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

A blue picture of three people together in a circle, under which is the word “Workers.” In the upper left corner is the Certified B Corp symbol, and in the lower right an emblem saying “Best for the World 2021.”

node.text:
We're excited to announce that #KingArthurBaking Company has been recognized as #BFTW2021! This means we scored in the top 5% of one of the five impact areas assessed as part of the B Corp certification process. We're proud to be Best For The World™ and a part of the global #BCorp community.

One unique benefit offered to our employee-owners is that every year, we're allotted 40 hours of paid volunteer time. In 2020, there were over 6,000 collective hours spent volunteering across our company! Learn more about King Arthur's volunteer program and check out the full Best for the World 2021 list by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking.

node.accessibility_caption: A blueberry pie with two slices removed and served on small plates. Photo by King Arthur Baking.

node.text: Perfect blueberry pie filling … without an oven? The beauty of fresh blueberries is the juicy “pop” as you bite into them. This deliciously satisfying feature is usually lost in pie, as they take on a soft, squishy texture. Here’s the good news: you can have your pie and eat it too. Check out our blog at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking for the secret to creating fresh blueberry pie, and share yours with #KingArthurBaking.

node.accessibility_caption: Brownies that have been cut into diamond shapes, on a piece of brown parchment paper with a cup of coffee next to it. -Photo shared by King Arthur Baking

node.text: The secret to making seriously incredible brownies? Almond flour! In this naturally #GrainFree recipe, our Baking Sugar Alternative makes these ultra-moist and fudgy brownies a sugar-free treat. They’re perfectly Sweet, Not Sugary. Find this and our collection of other Sweet Not Sugary recipes at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your brownies with #KingArthurBaking
